<subSubSection id="C35552F7FF90BF38A59949ED41AE1EF5" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF0017CFF90BF38A59949ED41AE1EF5" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF90BF38A59949ED43581F85" bold="true" box="[199,324,222,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Comment.</emphasis>
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF90BF38A7D249EC415C1F85" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[652,832,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisissimum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF90BF38A7D249EC415C1F85" box="[652,832,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">L. excisissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF90BF38A1CD49EC46F51F84" box="[1171,1257,223,249]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF90BF38A1A549ED478D1F85" author="Assing, V." box="[1275,1425,222,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">Assing 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The above record from 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF90BF38A4C1483143EC1E61" box="[415,496,258,284]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Xizang</collectingRegion>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4F7AFFFF90BF38A7E4483046191E61" authority="Assing, 2012" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2012" box="[698,1029,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisissimum">
<emphasis id="B93BDD6EFF90BF38A7E4483041701E61" box="[698,876,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">L. excisissimum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDE7C8DFF90BF38A62F483146191E61" author="Assing, V." box="[881,1029,258,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref3564" refString="Assing, V. (2012) A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Bonn zoological Bulletin, 61, 49 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 61.2.413 - 453" type="journal article" year="2012">
Assing, 
<quantity id="4CB7AC99FF90BF38A693483146191E61" box="[973,1029,258,284]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11048" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" unit="in" value="2012.0">2012</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance (Fig. 2C) and aedeagal characters (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF90BF38A421481543E11E3D" box="[383,509,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[567,1013,1056,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-290@1.[566,1021,1052,1910]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lobrathium anatinum (A–C) and L. excisissimum (D–G). A female tergite VIII B female sternite VIII C female tergites IX–X. D male sternite VII E male sternite VIII F aedeagus in ventral view G aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm. FIGURE 2. Male habitus of Lobrathium spp. A L. biaculeatum B L. chengzhifeii C L. excisissimum. Scales: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524308" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524308/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Figs 1D–G</figureCitation>
) and separated only by somewhat without yellowish spot in middle and faint reflex of elytra, consider of it as the same species. The above record from 
<collectingRegion id="498BCF9EFF90BF38A6C2487941F11E19" box="[924,1005,330,356]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Xizang</collectingRegion>
represents a new province record and extends the distributional range about 
<quantity id="4CB7AC99FF90BF38A71A485D40851EF5" box="[580,665,366,392]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="245" unit="km" value="740.0">740 km</quantity>
northwestwards (
<figureCitation id="13741DF9FF90BF38A63E485D41B81EF5" box="[864,932,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 5–8" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1007,1031]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,416,984]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[415,1173,416,984]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5–8. Collecting sites. 5 habitats of Lobrathium anatinum in Guangxi 6 habitats of Lobrathium biaculeatum in Xizang 7 type locality of Lobrathium chengzhifeii 8 habitats of Lobrathium excisissimum in Xizang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524312/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="245">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
